caption: Really great atmosphere and the service was great. The food was really good. I had escargot (amazing), pot roast (reminded me of home) and creme brulee (probably the best I have had). You can get a low cost bottle of wine at the wine bar and they will cork it for you and serve you. Highly recommend!

Delicious food. It was really busy, and there was clearly a large party in the back, so the service was a bit inconsistent (we got our appetizer after finishing our entree). It was still a lovely meal.
Great vibe wonderful music and an  outstanding burger. The rest of the menu is pretty good as well.
Mike is the absolute best!
Owners are friendly funny and know their wine!  So far every recommendation given to me was spot on!  Love this place

I went there for a company event.  From beginning (booking space) to end (event day) Terry was very helpful and friendly.  The 5 course dinner with wine pairing was amazing. Each course was delicious and the wine and sake (loved this) paired nicely with each meal.  Thank you, HASR for making our event a success!

Food and service were excellent and owner was very attentive. Hasr was very busy with private functions, yet we were provided with prompt and friendly service as if we were the only guests at the restaurant.

Great food!  Great service! Great atmosphere!  You can buy your bottles of wine from their well stocked shop and have it with your dinner.  Parking can be a challenge in downtown, but not for HASR.  Lots of parking across the street and it's only a few bucks.  A must go to restaurant!
A mixture of American, Contemporary,  and local style cooking. I don't have a favorite dish yet.
Very nice and friendly atmosphere the music was very good the food was very good and the service was exceptional we will definitely return  and would highly recommend others to visit
Food was good ✔, ambiance sweet ✔, no cork fee for wine purchased next door ✔, and sweet harmonies by Ben and Maila!  ✔
Great food!  Didn't have room for dessert so we'll have to make yet another trip!
(Translated by Google) The customer service was good. The owner's dog was cute too.  (Original) 接客が良かった。オーナーの犬も可愛いかった。
Great food and drinks 👍 live music awesome 👍 mahalo

I was very disappointed by my meal. My friend and I went to try out this restaurant last week. Entering the place, which was pretty empty, it took us calling out to the bartender for a waiter to seat us. The decor was nice and fitted the French Bistro format. We ordered an appetizer of warm brie. We specifically asked that it come out before the meal. It came out with the meal. It was good, but it was a toss up of what I wanted to go cold. I ordered a ribeye steak, rare. It was cooked rare on one side and well for about 2/3rds of the steak. The frites were pre packaged frozen French fries, either that or they did a very good job of replicating the taste and texture of such. Bottle of wine was 40 dollars. Had the original price tag of 15 dollars still on the bottle. Overall the meal was very overpriced and poorly executed. I would not recommend going here for dinner.
Great selection of wines. The owner is very friendly.

Just celebrated my wife's birthday at this hidden gem. Delicious fare from appetizers to dessert Will definitely be back. They have a wine tasting room next to the restaurant where we purchased a few bottles to enjoy with our dinner. Terri, the owner was so gracious in making sure we had a great time...which we did. Mahalo nui!!
Comfortable local restaurant priced reasonably, with the adjacent wine shop.  Service on this day of visit was rather slow for some reason, but I'd repeat visiting here for food/ambiance.
Salmon was excellent. Service was great. Music was loud. Be careful walking to and from at night!
Very limited menu but quality food.

I love this place! The location is in Downtown, so parking is somewhat of a challenge... but there is a municipal parking lot across the street.  There is live local music in the bar area downstairs & that's nice! The seating is very tight (especially on busy nights), but the food is good... which makes up for it!  Staff is nice as well... close to Hawai'i Theater so you can grab a bite before the shows!

Granted I went on somewhat busy night, but the service was really slow. I really admired the ambience and would go again to give it another go on the outdoor patio. Great twinkly lights. The food was decent, but more expensive than I expected.
The pot roast is the best thing. Get it.

The service here can be bad and good, so don't let that stop you from going and from going back. The food has been uniformly good on our several visits there. It's air conditioned inside, and they have a courtyard outside but off the street, if that's your pleasure. It is a nice American restaurant without the tourists of Waikiki.
Had our Christmas party upstairs. It was okay.
Good food
had a wine tasting and had a great time .
Good food. Good, but slow service tonight. Kinda pricey. Would recommend and come back.
(Translated by Google) Great death  (Original) Great pupus

Complimentary wine tasting was great.  Dining nxt experience ok. 8i inexperienced waiter...apparently they had three seperate parties going on at same time.... --so tho effort was there...service fell short. & food wasnt what pictures looked like. The large bowl of clams & small tiny french loaf wasnt enough to soak up the soup. But would be charged for more bread. The cioppino was the same. Lacked a bit of lemon, zest n spices. Agsin, not enough bread. The Oslo bucco fell short from resembling the deliciousness of the photo shown....no bones or marrow ...jus 3 small pieces of soft meat. Nothing too special for the price. The risotto was good. Didnt ...like that we were given small skinny glasses for our old world french red we bought ....no goblets? "No, only for our wine off the menu'' we were told. What the hell?! I would have much rather understood that they were short glassware due to their busy parties. Not that we were essentially 'downgraded glass- patrons' becuz we decided to get wine from their wine store nxt door. Not to mention that he took our wine to open it for us and didnt bring us our cork. The tried to gives some other cork that didnt fit; as we decided we'd bring the rest home to enjoy in more appropriate glasses. The outdoor seating is all that was available to dine, which was fine but realized a table cloth or more established table settings would have been more appealing & appreciated. It certainly would have felt better paying the over priced costs for the meal & blended with the serene outdoor atmosphere of mini lights & mini waterfall.
Great little place to grab great food!
Always great food here. Not well known so it's easy to get a reservation.

One of the Best Locally Owned Bistros in Hawaii! WHY? HASR Wine Shop right next door with knowledgeable people who actually Drink wine. Wine tasting. DELICIOUS  food, menu changes often enough that you don't eat the same thing every year. Staff is attentive and friendly. Best of all you can bring your Own wine!
Nice small patio up front. Pricing on bill was a little more than on the menu. Burger cooked exactly how I asked. Mango mojitos would be much better with a house made mix. Friendly waitstaff.
Good friendly service. Great food.
Great food, wine and staff! Be sure to visit the wine shop for one of the largest selection of wine and sake.  Guaranteed to fine the perfect bottle for any occasion and price point!

Rather good medium priced restaurant nicely hidden away in a quaint courtyard. The food is usually very good for the price and you can buy wine at the associated store with an excellent selection and not be charged corkage at the restaurant. Solid option if you want good food in a nice athmosphere at a reasonable price.

Very nice, cozy place in Chinatown near the theater. Seafood, steak, pasta, salads and good bread. Live music on certain nights. No corking fee if wine is brought in from the wine store next door. Indoor and outdoor garden area for dining.
Mike Kakazu so informative, knowledgeable, and helpful.
Delicious food! Great atmosphere
Cool vibe...Fridays, Ben and Maila
Very good food, soundtrack.
Food was excellen as well as the service.  Why the 4 stars? Service felt a bit rushed at end of evening.
Delightful music with Shawn Pimental and Lehua Kalima Alvarez
A little bit of Europe in Hawaii.  Such a quaint and lovely place and it doesn't even try to be.  It just is.

Had the local fish special. Sadly, it was overcooked 😔  Very disappointing since this was listed as one of the best places to eat downtown.  But the service was great, setting (we sat outside) was inviting and overall ambience was good. Now if only the chef knew it doesn't take long to cook swordfish then we'd be golden.
Good food, drinks, and service. Nice location and live entertainment.

Had lunch on Tuesday. Great Food Great Service.  Had the Escargot. Thought I was back in Paris. Talked the ear off of Terry, Dave and Jocelyn. Great listeners. My apologies.  Want to do the Supper Club.
The food, ambiance and the entertaintment, are awesome!!!
Good wine selection. A bit on a pricier side, though. Free wine tastings every Tuesday and Friday featuring 4-6 samples.
Beautiful as Always!!!!
Has a great wine selection
Very good food with rough service that could use a bit of polishing.

Been going for years and loved it.went last month and the menus has changed very sad, I will keep looking to see if things get beter.
Kind of pricy but the food is better than most. Also close to the parking structures.
All their food is great, went there often to celebrate special occasions with the wifey. Go next door and pick up a bottle of wine and sit down and have some great foods.
Awesome.  Had the shrimp spring rolls. That was really good!  Veggie pasta was also really good. Entree portion size was enough for 2. Definitely coming back!
